$$\frac{1-x^2}{1+x^2}=\frac{1-\tan^2\theta}{1+\tan^2\theta}=\cos^2\theta(1-\tan^2\theta)=\cos^2\theta-\sin^2\theta=
\cos(2\theta).$$
Donc

$$f_2(x)=\Arccos(\cos(2\theta))=\left\{
\begin{array}{l}
2\theta\;\mbox{si}\;\theta\in\left[0,\frac{\pi}{2}\right[\\
